  "texts": [
    "In this relationship, increasing the buffer size also increases the replay capacity and the (possible) age of the policy.",
    "In this way, the replay ratio remains constant.",
    "However, fixing the potential age of the oldest policy requires storing more transitions by the current policy to increase the replay capacity.",
    "In other words, it is necessary to decrease the number of function updates per number of interactions with the environment, which increases the number of agent interaction steps to store a more significant number of transitions from the current policy, which results in a decrease in replay ratio.",
    "On the other hand, keeping the replay capacity fixed (fixing the buffer size) decreases the age of the oldest policy but also requires more transitions, which will reduce the replay ratio."
